title: For Sale:  1969 Colt Python
postcontent: I have for sale one (1) Colt Python with a 4" barrel.  It has the original blued finish that is in beautiful condition and the original wooden grips.  The trigger has a "trigger shoe" installed on it to provide more surface area for the shooter. Of course, that is not something that messes up the value because it easily can be taken off and leaves no marks.  The overall condition of the gun is beautiful.  There is no marring in the bluing or damages to the metal anywhere.  The wood grips do have a few dent marks on the butt end, but nothing that is overwhelming or stands out.  You have to be inspecting it close to notice anything.This gun was owned by a gentleman that passed away a few months ago and he lived for his guns.  So this was very well taken care of.  He even left good notes in his journal.  After reviewing it, we found out that he purchased this gun from the original owner when he was in the service.  He did not have the box for it, but it was never put into a holster.  Kept in a gun rug and the previous owner said that he may have put 50 rounds through it, if that.  The past owner had down everytime he shot any of his firearms, in his journal.  There is only one listing for the Colt and he shot 25 rounds through it on May 9th of 1988.  Since then it has been in the gun rug and kept away from damp areas such as the basement.The cylinder is tight and the action is smooth as Tennessee Moonshine.  The cylinder also does not have that "wedding ring" marking on the cylinder, which also indicates it has been shot very little.  The family is going to put this in a gun auction in September and the auctioneer gave them an idea of what they could expect to get for it, based on the 5 or 6 he has sold this year, to be somewhere around the $2400.00-3100.00 because of its condition.  The family will place it in the auction as planned, but they would like to get the money for it ASAP so I have it listed on my account for anyone that is interested, to make an offer.  Please let me know as soon as you can.  I am going to leave it up for two weeks so please reach out to me if you are interested as soon as you can.  Thank you for looking and let me know if you have any questions and I will get them answered for you.Thanks for lookingUPDATE:  Gonna leave this up until it is sold or September 25th which is the day of the auction.  I have had 48 responses to this ad, so with that information I was able to lock in an "if sold before auction" price from the family.  $2675.00 will get you the Python.  We might accept a partial trade so if you have anything you would like to trade, feel free to ask.Thanks a title: For Sale:  Remington 720
postcontent: The Remington 720 was manufactured from 1940 - 1945.  Only 2,500 were manufactured.  The rifle has a controlled feed Mauser action and was made to compete with the Winchester Model 70.  Production was not continued after WWII.  This rifle is a representative example.  All the serial numbers match on the receiver, bolt, stock, and butt plate.  The bore is a little dark, but the rifling is clear and sharp.  There is some slight freckling on the barrel and receiver.  Stock is in good shape with a few dings and a slight chip on the bottom near the butt plate.  Rifle shoots great and is very accurate.
